LSTM (Long Short-Term Memory) — "The LSTM produces a hidden vector of size 512 at the final timestep, followed by LayerNorm , Dropout , and a fully connected layer that maps to the 256-channel latent space."
GCN-LSTM-PI (physics-informed) — "The GCN-LSTM-PI pipeline processes the input graph sequences to predict the next latent frame, and these latent states are then decoded via the 2D convolutional autoencoder to reconstruct the predicted microstructure images."

features_quote:
Latent encoding concatenated with scalar composition value (per node) — "The timesteps are then converted into graphs, where each node represents one spatial position and contains a feature vector comprising a latent encoding concatenated with the scalar composition value."
257-dimensional node feature vector (256 latent features + global composition) — "Each node is assigned a 257-dimensional feature vector by concatenating the 256 latent features at that location with the global scalar composition value."
